Take a look at the following piece of code. What will be printed out?

```java
public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        StringBuilder sb = new StringBuilder("Chosen Magicians:");
        List<String> magicians = Arrays.asList("Harry", "Ron", "Luna", "Fred", "Ginny");
        magicians.forEach(magician -> {
            if (magician.length() < 5) {
                sb.append(" ").append(magician).append(";");
            }
        });
        System.out.println(sb);
    }
}
```

Have a look at the following code. Which of the statements are correct?
`Assumption:` There are no Wizards with the same first name, last name, and age.

```java
class Wizard {
    private String firstName;
    private String lastName;
    private int age;
    public Wizard(String firstName, String lastName, int age) {
        this.firstName = firstName;
        this.lastName = lastName;
        this.age = age;
    }
    @Override
    public boolean equals(Object obj) {
        if (obj == null || this.getClass() != obj.getClass()) {
            return false;
        }
        Wizard wizard = (Wizard) obj;
        return firstName.equals(wizard.firstName) && lastName.equals(wizard.lastName) && age == wizard.age;
    }
    @Override
    public int hashCode() {
        return (age + 17) * firstName.hashCode() + lastName.hashCode();
    }
}
public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Wizard percy = new Wizard("Percy", "Weasley", 15);
        Wizard bill = new Wizard("Bill", "Weasley", 21);
        System.out.println(bill.hashCode() == percy.hashCode());
    }
}
```
